detaileddescription.para: This string will be inserted between each field as points are written.
This string will be written after each point. By default it's std::endl (the newline string).

This character may be used to enclose a field containing lots of characters that would otherwise need to be escaped. We have to know what it is so that we can escape it ourselves when we encounter the quote character inside fields.

detaileddescription.para: There are as many ways to write timestamps as there are programs to write them. We have our default (YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS) but sometimes you will need to specify some other format for interoperability.
This method sets a format string for timestamps using the flags in boost::date_time::time_facet.

briefdescription.para: Set the string representation for nulls.

detaileddescription.para: Property values that were never set are considered to hold a null value. This method lets you set how nulls will be written to disk. The default value is the empty string "".

simplesect.para: The representation of the null value

briefdescription.para: Set the decimal precision for writing coordinates.

detaileddescription.para: Internally, Tracktable stores coordinates as double-precision floating numbers. It is highly unlikely that trajectory data needs absolutely all of that precision. Since it takes up lots of space when we write data to disk, it is useful to be able to ask for reduced (or increased) precision.

briefdescription.para: Write trajectories of any type as delimited text.

detaileddescription.para: This class writes subclasses of tracktable::Trajectory (including the domain classes) to a stream as delimited text. It will write one trajectory per line. The resulting file will contain enough header information to reconstruct the trajectory exactly as long as the user asks for the correct class.
